   im talking about directX 8. that means everything that changed after directX 7. Other than video-3D-sound, most of this stuff is so old, its not worth talking about<br>
<br>
   For Progrogrammers. the main purpose is to take advantage of complex hardware like videocards, and all their cool features, although it deals with pretty much all hardware that allows input and output. Of course DirectX has competition, as you know. Most of whats not video is old and crappy.<br>
<br>
  directX is basically for multimedia. But as you say DirectPlay seems pretty neat, allowing peer to peer according to my friend, for other DirectX components to use. <br>
